- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science): Linearizability is a correctness criterion that can be formalized using logic. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms): The paper discusses the implementation and performance of linearizable data structures, which is a core topic in data structures and algorithms.
